      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A social worker was observing various community group dynamics to plan her community interventions better. During a meeting in one of the villages, she noticed that all members strictly followed whatever their leader said, without any discussion or questions. This type of obedience reminded her of her sociology lessons. In which type of social group do members usually follow the orders of the leader without question?</span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q8223737",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34639,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ans. C. Herd</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option C: </span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">The term &#39;<strong>herd&#39;</strong> in sociology refers to a type of <strong>social group</strong> where members often act in <strong>unison</strong>, following the <strong>dictates</strong> or <strong>directions</strong> of a <strong>leader </strong>or a <strong>dominant group</strong> member <strong>without question</strong> or <strong>critical analysis</strong>. This type of <strong>behavior</strong> is characterized by a <strong>lack of individual decision-making</strong> and a tendency to follow the <strong>crowd</strong> or the <strong>leader</strong>, often <strong>subduing</strong> personal opinions or <strong>critical thinking</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option A. &nbsp;Crowd</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: A <strong>group</strong> of <strong>people </strong>come <strong>together temporarily</strong>, for a <strong>short period</strong>, motivated by a <strong>common interest</strong> or <strong>curiosity</strong>. The <strong>crowd lacks</strong> <strong>internal organization and leadership.</strong> When the <strong>interest is over</strong>, the <strong>crowd disperses. </strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option B. Mob:&nbsp;</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Is essentially a <strong>crowd</strong> but has a <strong>leader</strong> who <strong>forces</strong> the <strong>members</strong> into <strong>action</strong>. There may be a <strong>symbol</strong> in the shape of a <strong>flag or slogan</strong>. The <strong>mob</strong> is <strong>more emotional</strong> than a crowd. It is <strong>unstable</strong> and <strong>without internal organization.</strong> When the purpose of the <strong>mob</strong> is <strong>achieved</strong>, the <strong>group disperses.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option D. Family: </span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">&nbsp;A group of <strong>biologically</strong> related <strong>individuals living together</strong> and <strong>eating</strong> from a <strong>common kitchen</strong>.&nbsp;<strong>Family</strong> is the <strong>primary unit</strong> of<strong> all societies</strong>.&nbsp;<strong>Family</strong> is the most <strong>powerful example</strong> of <strong>social cohesion.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">The Herd</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: A <strong>crowd with a leader</strong>, where the <strong>members</strong> of the <strong>group</strong> have to follow the <strong>orders</strong> of the <strong>leader without question.</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref:</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> Park 26<sup>th</sup> ed pg. 772</span></strong></span></span></p>",
