      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Dr. Shashi is a public health officer working in an urban health center in India. He is assessing the socioeconomic status of families in his area to allocate resources appropriately. He decided to use the Modified Kuppuswamy socioeconomic scale for his assessment. A junior intern accompanying him asks about the components considered in the Modified Kuppuswamy scale. Which of the following is NOT a component of the Modified Kuppuswamy socioeconomic scale?</span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q6881878",
